 of interest to MCH &amp; availability of information from online epidemiologic data tools. Students are introduced to 2 data tools: <a href="https://www.marchofdimes.org/peristats/Peristats.aspx">Peristats from the March of Dimes</a> &amp; <a href="https://wonder.cdc.gov/">CDC Wonder from the Centers for Disease Control &amp; Prevention</a>. In their groups, student generate a Data Brief modeled after the <a href="https://www.cdc.gov/nchs/products/databriefs.htm">National Center for Health Statistics&rsquo; (NCHS) Data Brief Reports</a>. A post-project survey is administered to students to assess knowledge &amp; skill development in MCH course content &amp; surveillance. </p><ul>  <li>Lecture Slides (pdf):<strong> </strong><a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="'Public Health Surveillance' (opens in a new tab)" href="../files/2020/05/Project-Poster-Presentation.pdf">&ldquo;Public Health Surveillance&rdquo;</a></li>  <li>Handout: <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="'Instructions for Navigating HP2020 Website' (opens in a new tab)" href="../files/2020/05/Instructions-for-Navigating-HP2020-Website.pdf">&ldquo;Instructions for Navigating HP2020 Website&rdquo;</a></li>  <li><a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="Data Brief Assignment Instructions (opens in a new tab)" href="../files/2020/05/Data-Brief-Assignment-Instructions.pdf">Data Brief Assignment Instructions</a></li>  <li><a href="../files/2020/05/Data-Brief-Rubric.pdf" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="Data Brief Rubric (opens in a new tab)">Data Brief Rubric</a></li>  <li><a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="Pre-/Post-Project Survey (opens in a new tab)" href="../files/2020/05/Pre-Post-Project-Survey.pdf">Pre-/Post-Project Survey</a></li>  <li><a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="Project Poster Presentation (opens in a new tab)" href="../files/2020/05/Project-Poster-Presentation.pdf">Project Poster Presentation</a></li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p></div></div><?php include('../../../incl/f